    "breadcrumb": "Internship Report",
    "content": "An overview of the internship and the development of the Smart Media Analytics project, broken down into weekly milestones with specific objectives:\nWeek 1: AWS Basics: Familiarized with the AWS ecosystem, practiced core services, and surveyed project directions. Week 2: Lambda \u0026 VPC: Researched and configured Amazon VPC network infrastructure, Subnets, and AWS Lambda. Week 3: Project Orientation: Onboarded at the company, learned internal workflows, and defined the project direction. Week 4: Backend \u0026 Docker: Initialized the FastAPI Backend structure, practiced Docker packaging, and explored ECR/ECS Fargate. Week 5: Database \u0026 API: Integrated PostgreSQL and Redis databases, and finalized the design of core management APIs. Week 6: AI Pipeline \u0026 Testing: Deployed AI services via Docker, synchronized the development environment, and fully tested the Backend. Week 7: Vector Store \u0026 Media: Completed the asynchronous AI pipeline (Scene, Image Caption, Transcription) and integrated ChromaDB. Week 8: Frontend Init: Built the Frontend platform with React, managed centralized States, and made the first API connections. Week 9: Bedrock \u0026 WebSocket: Connected AWS Bedrock, handled real-time uploads via WebSocket, and optimized Vector Embeddings. Week 10: Dashboard \u0026 Audio: Built the Audio Waveform, finalized the interactive Dashboard, and adjusted AWS architecture based on feedback. Week 11: End-to-End \u0026 UI/UX: Connected the E2E AI pipeline, packaged for Fargate, and overhauled the UI to an App-like standard. Week 12: CI/CD \u0026 Deployment: Automated CI/CD, set up CloudWatch monitoring, and completed the comprehensive A-Z Workshop documentation.",
